bug.short_desc: capture parameter not taken into consideration when an event is fired

long_desc.thetext:
when an event is fired in the qx.event.handler.Element class, the _onNative method is called. inside it, it further calls fireNonBubblingEvent method in the qx.event.Registration class. there, the manager is obtained for the target and the hasListener method is called on it [qx.event.Manager] with capture parameter always set to false. inside hasListener a key is computed based on capture in order to get the listeners from a map. problem is that if an event is registered with capture=true, it is never found in the map due to the fact that the key for the map takes into account the capture.
I propose to get the capture event parameter in the _onNative method and pass it to fireNonBubblingEvent and next to hasListener, so we can get the listener function.
you can reproduce the bug following these steps: - create a bom application. - in the html add an image - in the onReady event handler add this code: var img = qx.bom.Collection.id("special"); img.addListener("load",function(){alert('event fired')},img,true);
build it, run it, and the event is never fired. change the last parameter to false and you get the alert.
Or download the attached zip , it contains the bom application already.
